17: Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, JDBC, JDBC Driver - How They Are Connected
================================================================================

Spring Data JPA:

    Spring Data JPA ek abstraction layer hai jo relational databases ko access
    karne ke liye use hoti hai.

    Hum repository methods call karte hain:

        userRepository.findById(1L);
        userRepository.save(user);

    Spring Data JPA directly database se baat nahi karta.
    Under the hood, ye Hibernate ko use karta hai.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Hibernate:

    Hibernate ek ORM tool hai.

    ORM = Object Relational Mapping

    Hibernate ka kaam hai:

        Java objects/entities ko database tables se map karna.

    Example:

        User class  ->  users table

    Hibernate repository method /JPQL ko SQL query me convert karta hai.

    Example:

        userRepository.findById(1L);

    Internally SQL ban sakti hai:

        SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1;

    SQL execute karne ke liye Hibernate JDBC ka use karta hai.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JDBC:

    JDBC Java ka standard database API hai.

    Hibernate JDBC API ke through database operations perform karta hai.

    JDBC concepts:

        - Connection
        - PreparedStatement
        - ResultSet

    But JDBC khud database-specific communication nahi karta.

    Actual database-specific communication JDBC Driver karta hai.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JDBC Driver:

    JDBC Driver database-specific implementation hota hai.

    Example:

        MySQL ke liye:
            MySQL JDBC Driver

        PostgreSQL ke liye:
            PostgreSQL JDBC Driver

    JDBC Driver ka kaam hai:

        JDBC calls ko database-specific protocol me convert karna.

    Example:

        JDBC call:
            executeQuery()

        MySQL Driver:
            MySQL protocol ke through query MySQL server ko bhejta hai.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Complete Flow:

    Application Code
        |
        v
    Spring Data JPA Repository
        |
        v
    Hibernate ORM
        |
        v
    JDBC API
        |
        v
    JDBC Driver
        |
        v
    TCP connection + Database-specific protocol
        |
        v
    Database Server

Default ports :

    MySQL:
        Default port: 3306

    PostgreSQL:
        Default port: 5432

    Redis:
        Default port: 6379

